      "message": "I\u0027m guessing you have the JSON written a certain way because it matches the docs or makes the most sense that way.\n\nHowever, just as an FYI, the JSON can contain a simple bool/string/int, an array, or an object.\n\nSo you could just have the array without the enclosing object:\n```\n    const auto sensorConfig \u003d R\"(\n        [\n            {\n                \"path_suffix\": \"_0\",\n                \"threshold\": 30,\n                \"has_target\": true\n            },\n            {\n                \"path_suffix\": \"_1\",\n                \"threshold\": 30,\n                \"has_target\": false,\n                \"factor\": 0.625,\n                \"offset\": 1100\n            }\n        ]\n      )\"_json;\n```\n\nAnd then pass that element directly to getSensorDefs().",
